01:07:19.050 --> 01:07:20.000
And next year,
they do it, right?

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:21.791
And that's-- and that's
the way it happens.

01:07:21.791 --> 01:07:24.105
And I'm kind of a little
bit excited [INAUDIBLE].

01:07:24.105 --> 01:07:25.480
But this is roughly
what happens.

01:07:25.480 --> 01:07:28.050
I mean, you can make all the
nice frameworks you want.

01:07:28.050 --> 01:07:29.300
You [INAUDIBLE] to the target.

01:07:29.300 --> 01:07:31.550
But this explains what happens.

01:07:31.550 --> 01:07:33.810
Someone cares about this number.

01:07:33.810 --> 01:07:36.880
They force you to think about
what's the best way to do it.

01:07:36.880 --> 01:07:38.435
And you go back to
your team and try

01:07:38.435 --> 01:07:40.810
to find some sort of middle
ground between what you think

01:07:40.810 --> 01:07:43.880
is doable, what you
really think you can do,

01:07:43.880 --> 01:07:46.630
and your manager and the
CEO tries to stretch you

01:07:46.630 --> 01:07:47.920
beyond that limit.

01:07:47.920 --> 01:07:50.344
So you do not just set a
number that makes no sense.

01:07:50.344 --> 01:07:52.510
Because everyone's going
to put a number that I know

01:07:52.510 --> 01:07:53.880
I'm going to meet.

01:07:53.880 --> 01:07:55.160
And the CEO knows this.

01:07:55.160 --> 01:07:58.422
And because of that, he
says, I want double of that.

01:07:58.422 --> 01:08:00.060
And you play the
game of tension.

01:08:00.060 --> 01:08:01.050
And you miss one year.

01:08:01.050 --> 01:08:05.030
You don't get the bonus and
make sure you do a better job.

01:08:05.030 --> 01:08:06.926
That process is exactly
the same process

01:08:06.926 --> 01:08:09.680
you should go for
environment targets, right?

01:08:09.680 --> 01:08:11.370
It's exactly the same process.

01:08:11.370 --> 01:08:16.026
I mentioned at the end of this
long rant one important thing.

01:08:16.026 --> 01:08:18.710
Your bonus is set
to this, right?

01:08:18.710 --> 01:08:20.560
So that means money.

01:08:20.560 --> 01:08:22.660
But some sort of incentive
is set to this process.

01:08:22.660 --> 01:08:29.810
If there's no incentive or
penalty, nothing gets done.

01:08:29.810 --> 01:08:33.160
So you can get, in the
short term, some things.

01:08:33.160 --> 01:08:36.742
But in other things, you need
to provide specific targets.

01:08:36.742 --> 01:08:38.200
So this is where,
again, we go back

01:08:38.200 --> 01:08:41.250
to-- you want to do carbon
footprint emissions?

01:08:41.250 --> 01:08:45.370
You have to tie it to something
that the person can do.

01:08:45.370 --> 01:08:49.270
For example, if you want to
reduce 20% of your emissions

01:08:49.270 --> 01:08:52.180
or go to the same level
of emissions as 2020

01:08:52.180 --> 01:08:55.540
based on the 2001
baseline, then you

01:08:55.540 --> 01:08:58.220
have to connect those
emissions to something

01:08:58.220 --> 01:08:59.918
you can take action
on-- energy use.

01:08:59.918 --> 01:09:00.418
Right.

01:09:00.418 --> 01:09:03.904
STUDENT: Don't you run the
risk, though, of kind of,

01:09:03.904 --> 01:09:10.387
I don't know, questioning
the integrity of the process?

01:09:10.387 --> 01:09:12.470
Because then you could
have engineering in the way

01:09:12.470 --> 01:09:14.390
you're reporting or measuring.

01:09:14.390 --> 01:09:17.000
And if you tie some sort
of financial incentive

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:20.040
to the goals, then
there is the potential

01:09:20.040 --> 01:09:23.890
to have a lot of effort to have
good results on paper but maybe

01:09:23.890 --> 01:09:26.719
not necessarily to be driving
more [? real results. ?]

01:09:26.719 --> 01:09:28.760
STUDENT: PROFESSOR: So
that's talk about-- that's

01:09:28.760 --> 01:09:30.630
a really good point.

01:09:30.630 --> 01:09:33.950
So the companies that
are successful at this,

01:09:33.950 --> 01:09:36.260
they-- somehow the
measurement systems

01:09:36.260 --> 01:09:39.130
need to be as reliable as
possible to avoid that problem.

01:09:39.130 --> 01:09:42.609
Because if yo don't have a good
way to measure the progress,

01:09:42.609 --> 01:09:44.500
then you can fudge the numbers.

01:09:44.500 --> 01:09:46.250
So you have to connect
it back to whatever

01:09:46.250 --> 01:09:48.640
metric of your
business you can get

01:09:48.640 --> 01:09:50.870
actual reliable information on.

01:09:50.870 --> 01:09:53.290
And I think that's why the
leading companies, I think

01:09:53.290 --> 01:09:55.580
that's why they do
better is that, sure, we

01:09:55.580 --> 01:09:57.830
want to do carbon footprint
and we do with [INAUDIBLE]

01:09:57.830 --> 01:10:00.700
this big [INAUDIBLE]
protocol CDP report.

01:10:00.700 --> 01:10:03.090
But somehow as
they go down, they

01:10:03.090 --> 01:10:06.720
tie this to number of miles
driven on my car, number

01:10:06.720 --> 01:10:10.760
of kilowatt hours of my-- so
that process of kind of somehow

01:10:10.760 --> 01:10:13.180
connecting these goals
and measurement systems,

01:10:13.180 --> 01:10:15.781
that I think is the hard part
that companies take a long time

01:10:15.781 --> 01:10:16.280
to develop.

01:10:16.280 --> 01:10:18.480
Because information
you need to measure

01:10:18.480 --> 01:10:19.540
you may not be capturing.

01:10:19.540 --> 01:10:22.120
So you have to build, let's
say, that knowledge internally

01:10:22.120 --> 01:10:23.260
and then eventually try it.

01:10:23.260 --> 01:10:23.870
But I agree.

01:10:23.870 --> 01:10:27.330
If you do have some sort of
connection to the real business

01:10:27.330 --> 01:10:32.420
operations, you cannot really
set credible targets and tie it

01:10:32.420 --> 01:10:32.920
to money.

01:10:32.920 --> 01:10:34.340
And I'll give you
another example.

01:10:34.340 --> 01:10:36.256
I know you have a question
before we move to--

01:10:36.256 --> 01:10:39.640
STUDENT: [INAUDIBLE] measurement
like in the Palm Oil case

01:10:39.640 --> 01:10:43.405
and also with Chevron to do
third party verifications

01:10:43.405 --> 01:10:48.668
of things just to verify
before they award incentives

01:10:48.668 --> 01:10:52.240
or peform the
bonuses or whatever.

01:10:52.240 --> 01:10:56.860
PROFESSOR: So not
all the-- so not

01:10:56.860 --> 01:10:59.370
all the performance
gives bonuses,

01:10:59.370 --> 01:11:02.160
but they do have an
impact on your evaluation.

01:11:02.160 --> 01:11:04.860
So let's suppose you don't have
to try as a bonus something,

01:11:04.860 --> 01:11:07.030
but you have to meet
certain criteria.

01:11:07.030 --> 01:11:08.530
And if you don't
meet them, you know

01:11:08.530 --> 01:11:09.988
there's a risk that
your job is not

01:11:09.988 --> 01:11:12.160
going to be there for you
in two, three, four years.

01:11:12.160 --> 01:11:13.227
No one expects so.

01:11:13.227 --> 01:11:15.560
I mean, that was your question--
was that your question?

01:11:15.560 --> 01:11:16.690
STUDENT: I'm just saying--

01:11:16.690 --> 01:11:17.690
PROFESSOR: As a comment.

01:11:17.690 --> 01:11:21.882
STUDENT: Yeah, one way to ensure
that the system isn't being

01:11:21.882 --> 01:11:23.460
exploited is that companies--

01:11:23.460 --> 01:11:24.120
PROFESSOR: Yeah, third party.

01:11:24.120 --> 01:11:25.080
STUDENT: --use third part--

01:11:25.080 --> 01:11:26.320
PROFESSOR: Yeah, absolutely.

01:11:26.320 --> 01:11:28.030
So third party
verification is one way

01:11:28.030 --> 01:11:30.050
to try to achieve
that balance and make

01:11:30.050 --> 01:11:31.620
sure you have a third--
especially as you go deeper

01:11:31.620 --> 01:11:32.495
in your supply chain.

01:11:32.495 --> 01:11:35.254
But I do want to emphasize
that to be serious--

01:11:35.254 --> 01:11:37.420
I"m not saying that these
companies are not serious,

01:11:37.420 --> 01:11:41.040
but to be able to fully embed
it to your business capabilities

01:11:41.040 --> 01:11:45.150
as a company, somehow you need
to set goals and targets that

01:11:45.150 --> 01:11:47.700
are tied to ways that
are credible measures.

01:11:47.700 --> 01:11:50.900
You cannot just be do your-
everyone does their estimation

01:11:50.900 --> 01:11:52.482
of CO2, right?

01:11:52.482 --> 01:11:55.740
It needs to be, I
have a CO2 calculator

01:11:55.740 --> 01:11:59.190
that is somewhere in my system
that I can click a button

01:11:59.190 --> 01:12:01.170
and know how things are going.

01:12:01.170 --> 01:12:04.542
If I cannot do that, then this
is your CSR report that happens

01:12:04.542 --> 01:12:05.500
at the end of the year.

01:12:07.919 --> 01:12:09.710
Let me just differentiate
what I just said.

01:12:09.710 --> 01:12:11.180
So everyone can
come after the fact

01:12:11.180 --> 01:12:14.585
that I can do an estimation of
CO2, hire MIT, hire Stanford,

01:12:14.585 --> 01:12:17.470
and I can go in and spend
six months, right, and do--

01:12:17.470 --> 01:12:19.670
this how much CO2 you save.

01:12:19.670 --> 01:12:22.040
Great, but that doesn't
mean that the company is

01:12:22.040 --> 01:12:23.330
doing anything right.

01:12:23.330 --> 01:12:26.550
If you're a manager, you have
to get a report every semester,

01:12:26.550 --> 01:12:28.200
every quarter, and
this is how we're

01:12:28.200 --> 01:12:29.537
doing so you can take action.

01:12:29.537 --> 01:12:30.995
And the only way
you can do that is

01:12:30.995 --> 01:12:34.500
to connect that measurement
of environmental performance

01:12:34.500 --> 01:12:36.500
to something that you are
collecting in your day

01:12:36.500 --> 01:12:41.420
to day operation, whatever
it is-- energy use, again,

01:12:41.420 --> 01:12:45.120
number of tons of miles
you sold to waste disposal.

01:12:45.120 --> 01:12:46.090
Something, right?

01:12:46.090 --> 01:12:48.554
And someone has to figure
out how that number connects

01:12:48.554 --> 01:12:49.970
with the environmental
goal you're

01:12:49.970 --> 01:12:54.450
trying to achieve and set
that target to that metric.

01:12:54.450 --> 01:12:56.780
This process is
what is difficult.

01:12:56.780 --> 01:13:01.050
And that's why the measurement
is kind of the tricky part

01:13:01.050 --> 01:13:04.200
because companies are
not used to measure.

01:13:04.200 --> 01:13:06.330
And if you do not do
that, the only thing

01:13:06.330 --> 01:13:10.670
you have is a great
CSR reporting machine.

01:13:10.670 --> 01:13:12.920
You are not really
changing your business

01:13:12.920 --> 01:13:15.120
or your suppliers' businesses.

01:13:15.120 --> 01:13:18.140
You have a great CSR
reporting, which is needed.

01:13:18.140 --> 01:13:19.490
It's a precondition.

01:13:19.490 --> 01:13:20.520
Unless you know how
to do it yourself,

01:13:20.520 --> 01:13:21.570
you cannot put it
in your metric.

01:13:21.570 --> 01:13:22.480
You have to trust it.

01:13:22.480 --> 01:13:24.074
You have to develop
the expertise.

01:13:24.074 --> 01:13:25.490
You have to have
the right people.

01:13:25.490 --> 01:13:28.432
You have the SAP systems to be
rolled out whatever you use it.

01:13:28.432 --> 01:13:29.390
Someone needs to do it.

01:13:29.390 --> 01:13:31.410
If you don't have
it, you cannot do it.

01:13:31.410 --> 01:13:32.749
And this goes back to suppliers.

01:13:32.749 --> 01:13:34.540
And we'll talk about
suppliers in a second.

01:13:34.540 --> 01:13:36.915
But is there any questions or
comments about what I said?

01:13:36.915 --> 01:13:39.397
I want to make
sure this is clear.

01:13:39.397 --> 01:13:41.730
STUDENT: A lot of the incentive
