01:13:43.521 --> 01:13:45.740
They give out 20
shares or whatever.

01:13:45.740 --> 01:13:47.890
And there's a conflict
between getting that share

01:13:47.890 --> 01:13:50.237
price to increase and
doing the right thing.

01:13:50.237 --> 01:13:51.945
For companies that
have target incentives

01:13:51.945 --> 01:13:54.660
that are stock driven, do
you have any suggestions

01:13:54.660 --> 01:13:57.154
for setting goals and targets?

01:13:57.154 --> 01:13:58.820
PROFESSOR: That's
where-- the only thing

01:13:58.820 --> 01:14:01.550
I like there is the Dow Jones
sustainable index even though I

01:14:01.550 --> 01:14:03.540
hate that index.

01:14:03.540 --> 01:14:06.170
It's a great index because
at least people connect it

01:14:06.170 --> 01:14:07.726
to stock prices in
a more direct way.

01:14:07.726 --> 01:14:09.850
Even though the connection
is because of sales MIT,

01:14:09.850 --> 01:14:13.240
the majority is revenue-- like,
30% of [INAUDIBLE] is revenue.

01:14:13.240 --> 01:14:15.060
But they have at
least some metrics

01:14:15.060 --> 01:14:17.750
that are environmental
transparency that people try

01:14:17.750 --> 01:14:19.760
to connect with stock prices.

01:14:19.760 --> 01:14:22.890
I have to say that
public companies have

01:14:22.890 --> 01:14:26.500
a really hard time to make
these aspirational goals

01:14:26.500 --> 01:14:28.670
because they're not
connected to value directly.

01:14:28.670 --> 01:14:32.130
This long term,
short term trade off

01:14:32.130 --> 01:14:35.980
that prevents them of embedding
a good sustainability practice

01:14:35.980 --> 01:14:37.380
is very hard.

01:14:37.380 --> 01:14:40.280
Let me give you
the other answer.

01:14:40.280 --> 01:14:44.310
Who was talking here?

01:14:44.310 --> 01:14:47.630
Seventh Generation said
that, although they're not

01:14:47.630 --> 01:14:48.660
publicly traded.

01:14:48.660 --> 01:14:51.240
They said, our
shareholders know they're

01:14:51.240 --> 01:14:54.470
getting lower return of
reinvestment than other.

01:14:54.470 --> 01:14:58.340
And they buy our stock with
that understanding, that?

01:14:58.340 --> 01:15:03.310
Unilever shareholders know that
Unilever is making some trade

01:15:03.310 --> 01:15:06.200
offs for the long term and
they're buying their stock.

01:15:06.200 --> 01:15:08.680
Now, the promise
and the belief is

01:15:08.680 --> 01:15:12.110
that they're going to recover
that value over the long run.

01:15:12.110 --> 01:15:14.626
But ultimately
speaking, I do not

01:15:14.626 --> 01:15:16.500
think there's a good
connection you can make.

01:15:16.500 --> 01:15:17.980
Allow me to be totally honest.

01:15:17.980 --> 01:15:22.270
I have not seen it that you can
make a real concrete connection

01:15:22.270 --> 01:15:24.780
between stock price
and sustainability

01:15:24.780 --> 01:15:25.852
in the short term.

01:15:25.852 --> 01:15:27.310
What I've heard
the argument, which

01:15:27.310 --> 01:15:29.930
I think is a real
argument, is a company that

01:15:29.930 --> 01:15:33.860
can develop this kind
of system is a company

01:15:33.860 --> 01:15:36.620
that must have a really
sophisticated management, which

01:15:36.620 --> 01:15:39.100
means this company must be
run by smart people, which

01:15:39.100 --> 01:15:41.860
means this company must
be making some good money.

01:15:41.860 --> 01:15:43.846
But this is a very
indirect argument.

01:15:43.846 --> 01:15:44.970
It's not a direct argument.

01:15:44.970 --> 01:15:45.790
Oh, you did this?

01:15:45.790 --> 01:15:47.040
You can get money back.

01:15:47.040 --> 01:15:50.310
It's more, if you're willing
to pull this off and not

01:15:50.310 --> 01:15:54.250
crash your business, that means
that you are really well run

01:15:54.250 --> 01:15:56.310
management company
and we believe

01:15:56.310 --> 01:15:59.430
that you are going to be
able to achieve other things.

01:15:59.430 --> 01:16:01.501
Because besides all
your complexity,

01:16:01.501 --> 01:16:03.750
you have been able to embed
sustainability in your day

01:16:03.750 --> 01:16:04.500
to day operations.

01:16:04.500 --> 01:16:06.445
Is that-- it's kind
of a poor answer.

01:16:06.445 --> 01:16:08.100
STUDENT: --Wall Street is
going to let you get away

01:16:08.100 --> 01:16:09.230
with it for so long, right?

01:16:09.230 --> 01:16:10.646
PROFESSOR: Yeah,
for so long, yes.

01:16:10.646 --> 01:16:13.520
At some point, that's kind of
an argument of capabilities

01:16:13.520 --> 01:16:16.538
more than an argument of
delivering results is just,

01:16:16.538 --> 01:16:17.996
you should be able
to do this well.

