01:17:25.673 --> 01:17:27.590
I think that's possible.

01:17:27.590 --> 01:17:28.700
Yes, it's always possible.

01:17:28.700 --> 01:17:30.490
Let me actually
say two more things

01:17:30.490 --> 01:17:33.160
on setting goals and targets.

01:17:33.160 --> 01:17:38.240
So I'm trying to
emphasize this point.

01:17:38.240 --> 01:17:40.230
Supplier selection--
let's talk about when

01:17:40.230 --> 01:17:42.122
you want to go to your
tier one suppliers

01:17:42.122 --> 01:17:43.330
and make them greener, right?

01:17:43.330 --> 01:17:46.840
And you want to really make
them part of your strategy.

01:17:46.840 --> 01:17:50.380
If there's no measure in your
scorecards to your supplier

01:17:50.380 --> 01:17:54.910
selection, this means nothing.

01:17:54.910 --> 01:17:57.960
So when the buyer is
sitting in the table

01:17:57.960 --> 01:18:01.860
and he has to make a decision
on which supplier to select

01:18:01.860 --> 01:18:08.530
and there's no metric there that
says sustainability, trust me.

01:18:08.530 --> 01:18:10.730
That person is going to
do their best effort.

01:18:10.730 --> 01:18:14.490
Now, the problem is if
you have never done it,

01:18:14.490 --> 01:18:15.534
how do you start?

01:18:15.534 --> 01:18:17.200
How do you start
putting a metric there?

01:18:17.200 --> 01:18:19.790
You have to give people--
educate them first.

01:18:19.790 --> 01:18:23.280
You have to first-- I recommend
you to measure this, right?

01:18:23.280 --> 01:18:25.640
It's not part of our
evaluation process.

01:18:25.640 --> 01:18:27.129
You do that for
two or three years.

01:18:27.129 --> 01:18:29.420
You first understand your
capability of your suppliers.

01:18:29.420 --> 01:18:30.677
You have to get to know them.

01:18:30.677 --> 01:18:31.760
You get their information.

01:18:31.760 --> 01:18:33.801
That's why the CDP report
actually is quite good.

01:18:33.801 --> 01:18:35.360
You have a structured processes.

01:18:35.360 --> 01:18:37.550
They start knowing, you
know, we should mention your

01:18:37.550 --> 01:18:38.490
[INAUDIBLE].

01:18:38.490 --> 01:18:38.991
Oh really?

01:18:38.991 --> 01:18:40.115
OK, let me start measuring.

01:18:40.115 --> 01:18:41.520
And the next year
they come back.

01:18:41.520 --> 01:18:43.390
I still do not
know how to do it.

01:18:43.390 --> 01:18:44.700
The next year, they come back.

01:18:44.700 --> 01:18:47.020
And eventually, they
get good at measuring.

01:18:47.020 --> 01:18:48.410
You do the same for waste.

01:18:48.410 --> 01:18:50.510
You do the same for the
things you care about.

01:18:50.510 --> 01:18:54.110
You have to somehow
teach them what it takes

01:18:54.110 --> 01:18:57.244
to measure what you care about.

01:18:57.244 --> 01:18:58.910
Once they have that
in a few iterations,

01:18:58.910 --> 01:19:01.630
then you can really start
putting it in a contract.

01:19:01.630 --> 01:19:04.810
And I think if you see
what companies have done--

01:19:04.810 --> 01:19:06.640
whom I was talking recently?

01:19:06.640 --> 01:19:12.220
Yes, this may not be public yet.

01:19:12.220 --> 01:19:14.650
So they have been asking
for their sustainability

01:19:14.650 --> 01:19:16.880
metric from their
suppliers for five years.

01:19:16.880 --> 01:19:19.720
And next year is
going to be mandatory.

01:19:19.720 --> 01:19:22.710
It's going to be a requirement
for buying products.

01:19:22.710 --> 01:19:25.440
It's a big CPG company-- huge.

01:19:25.440 --> 01:19:28.560
And they have done all the
traditional greenhouse gas

01:19:28.560 --> 01:19:30.760
metrics, waste metrics,
traditional ones.

01:19:30.760 --> 01:19:32.680
And they have always
said information for you

01:19:32.680 --> 01:19:34.452
to look into that information.

01:19:34.452 --> 01:19:36.410
Starting next year, it's
going to be mandatory.

01:19:36.410 --> 01:19:39.270
And if yo don't have it,
you're not our supplier.

01:19:39.270 --> 01:19:41.770
And in five years, they're
going to reduce by 20%.

01:19:41.770 --> 01:19:45.360
So I'm pointing out is that
there's a first phase where you

01:19:45.360 --> 01:19:47.120
just ask for the information.

01:19:47.120 --> 01:19:51.720
So people build their own metric
systems you cannot expect them

01:19:51.720 --> 01:19:53.770
to be sustainable if
you have never measured.

01:19:53.770 --> 01:19:56.350
So by asking your supplies
for the information,

01:19:56.350 --> 01:19:59.580
even though it's not in
the scorecard of selection,

01:19:59.580 --> 01:20:02.340
you start this cycle for them.

01:20:02.340 --> 01:20:04.810
This is what matters to me.

01:20:04.810 --> 01:20:06.540
When I'm buying
from you, I want you

01:20:06.540 --> 01:20:08.450
to tell me how much
energy you use,

01:20:08.450 --> 01:20:10.370
how much waste you generate.

01:20:10.370 --> 01:20:11.620
Oh, it matters to you?

01:20:11.620 --> 01:20:13.690
So I better start measuring it.

01:20:13.690 --> 01:20:16.820
You somehow start creating
this cycle with your suppliers.

01:20:16.820 --> 01:20:20.710
But only the moment where
you change this cycle into,

01:20:20.710 --> 01:20:24.730
I bring it into your
procurement organization

01:20:24.730 --> 01:20:29.210
as a decision making process
like price, quality, safety,

01:20:29.210 --> 01:20:31.530
CO2 reduction.

01:20:31.530 --> 01:20:36.680
Only at that time it really
becomes part of your business.

01:20:36.680 --> 01:20:39.350
Otherwise, it's
just good wishing.

01:20:39.350 --> 01:20:40.860
That is a long process.

01:20:40.860 --> 01:20:43.284
So what I just said
is a five year cycle,

01:20:43.284 --> 01:20:45.200
especially when you talk
about a large company

01:20:45.200 --> 01:20:46.590
with many, many suppliers.

01:20:46.590 --> 01:20:49.710
Great example of these--
Natura in Brazil.

01:20:49.710 --> 01:20:54.287
They have specific targets for
the supplies of CO2 reduction.

01:20:54.287 --> 01:20:55.370
They have their templates.

01:20:55.370 --> 01:20:58.590
This is how you fill it
out, how much energy you do.

01:20:58.590 --> 01:21:00.472
This is exactly what
you expect from them.

01:21:00.472 --> 01:21:02.055
And this is exactly
how much reduction

01:21:02.055 --> 01:21:03.840
I expect from you year to year.

01:21:03.840 --> 01:21:07.090
And if you don't get it,
you're no longer my supplier.

01:21:07.090 --> 01:21:09.135
But this took some time,
even though they're

01:21:09.135 --> 01:21:13.680
a very sustainable
company as a whole.

01:21:13.680 --> 01:21:15.850
And this is what
you do internally.

01:21:15.850 --> 01:21:17.790
And of course, always
you have to stay

01:21:17.790 --> 01:21:21.120
in tuned with your moral
compass, your partner that

01:21:21.120 --> 01:21:25.630
tell you which are the
issues that you think,

01:21:25.630 --> 01:21:28.370
which areas of the world you
have to be worried about that

01:21:28.370 --> 01:21:30.390
could have more
regulation, right?

01:21:30.390 --> 01:21:32.030
How can you make sure
your reputation--

01:21:32.030 --> 01:21:34.880
you have to defend
all those dimensions.

01:21:34.880 --> 01:21:40.270
So this is, I think, how you
can develop long term strategy.

01:21:40.270 --> 01:21:42.250
So we have to wrap up now.

01:21:42.250 --> 01:21:46.940
But on Wednesday, we're going
to hear someone from a company

